This paper deals with fair division, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the allocation of goods, which can be modeled using data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of random distributions and probability also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
